    detailedExplanationExpert: `The Gambler's Fallacy is profitable for casinos because it increases the total amount wagered (more bets × negative expected value = more casino profit). Additionally, players who believe in the fallacy often increase bet sizes after losses (Martingale-style), which further increases the expected loss per session.`,
