    detailedExplanationIntermediate: `The detective inverts: P(blood type|killer) is not P(killer|blood type). The 2% prevalence means 100,000 people in a city of 5 million share it. The suspect is one of 100,000 potential matches. The blood on the victim is additional evidence, but the detective's 98% figure is mathematically unjustified.`,
    detailedExplanationExpert: `The detective conflates the complement of a trait's frequency with posterior guilt probability. Even if the suspect uniquely matches the blood type, P(guilty|blood type + blood on victim) depends on P(blood type|innocent), the base rate of guilt, and the total probability of all evidence. The 98% figure is derived from 1 - 0.02, which has no valid Bayesian interpretation.`,
