    detailedExplanationExpert: `The expert commits the Prosecutor's Fallacy by directly substituting P(E|¬G) for P(¬G|E). Without computing P(E|G), the prior P(G), and the total P(E), the posterior is undefined. The expert's figure of 1/25,000 only describes the defect's false positive rate, not the posterior probability of innocence. The true probability depends on the total number of printers that could produce this defect.`,
