    concept: "Probability & Evidence",
    difficulty: 3,
    subLevel: SubLevel.EXPERT,
    question: `In R v. Towner (1996), the defendant was convicted of murder based partly on a 1 in 50,000 blood type match. The Court of Appeal quashed the conviction because the jury was not told that the match probability is NOT the same as:`,
