    concept: "Probability & Evidence",
    difficulty: 3,
    subLevel: SubLevel.EXPERT,
    question: `In a cold case DNA match, the forensic scientist testifies: "The probability of this DNA profile matching a random person is 1 in 1 billion. With 7 billion people on Earth, about 7 people match. The defendant is one of 7." This reasoning correctly avoids the Prosecutor's Fallacy because:`,
    options: ["It converts the match probability into an expected count of innocent matches", "It uses a Bayesian framework", "It acknowledges the base rate", "It computes the likelihood ratio"],
