    detailedExplanationExpert: `This is a portfolio-level survivorship bias. The investor's mental accounting excludes realized losses from the evaluation, treating only currently-held positions as evidence. This is identical to mutual fund survivorship bias where fund companies close poor-performing funds and only advertise successful ones.`,
