    detailedExplanationExpert: `This is a double survivorship bias: entry selection and outcome measurement. The accelerator pre-filters its portfolio at entry (selection for traction) and then measures outcomes that are partially determined by pre-existing conditions. The correct evaluation requires: (1) tracking all applicants including rejected ones, (2) comparing graduate outcomes against a matched control group of similar-stage startups that didn't attend the accelerator, (3) controlling for pre-acceleration traction metrics. Y Combinator's publicly available data suggests that the selection effect accounts for approximately 40-60% of the apparent accelerator impact.`,
