    detailedExplanationExpert: `This is a policy-outcome survivorship bias in urban studies. The "successful gentrification" criterion is itself a post-hoc selection that excludes negative outcomes. The correct methodology requires: (1) identifying all neighborhoods undergoing gentrification, (2) tracking outcomes for all residents including displaced ones, (3) measuring distributional effects across income groups, and (4) comparing against matched non-gentrifying neighborhoods. Urban research shows that gentrification effects are highly heterogeneous, with significant displacement that survivorship-filtered studies miss.`,
