    detailedExplanationIntermediate: `The 90% figure is a per-protocol result that excludes 40% of the enrolled population. If dropouts left due to treatment failure, the true remission rate among all patients is much lower (potentially 54% or less). The correct metric is intention-to-treat: remission among all randomized patients.`,
