    subLevel: SubLevel.EXPERT,
    question: `A study of "successful weight loss maintainers" (people who kept weight off for 5+ years) finds common habits among them and recommends those habits for everyone. What fallacy is this?`,
    options: ["Survivorship Bias", "Cherry-picking", "Gambler's Fallacy", "Hasty Generalization"],
    correct_option_index: 0,
    explanation: `The study only examines successful maintainers—people who tried the same habits but regained weight are invisible, so the habits may not actually cause maintenance.`,
