    subLevel: SubLevel.EXPERT,
    question: `A real estate investment trust (REIT) reports "average annual returns of 12%" but only includes properties currently in the portfolio—foreclosed and sold-at-a-loss properties were removed from the dataset. What fallacy is this?`,
    options: ["Survivorship Bias", "Gambler's Fallacy", "Prosecutor's Fallacy", "Cherry-picking"],
