    detailedExplanationExpert: `P(drug use|positive) = (0.98 × 0.05) / [(0.98 × 0.05) + (0.05 × 0.95)] ≈ 50.8%. Despite a highly accurate test, a positive yields only ~51% probability. The HR director treated test accuracy as the relevant probability instead of computing the posterior—textbook base-rate neglect with serious legal consequences.`,
